Referred to Committee on Education
SUMMARY—Revises provisions relating to emergency response in
schools. (BDR 36-1006)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: No.
Effect on the State: Contains Appropriation not included
in Executive Budget.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to emergency response; creating the Account for
the Nevada School Safety Data Grant Program within the
Division of Emergency Management of the Office of the
Military to award grants to law enforcement agencies to
procure school mapping data for public schools in this
State; prescribing certain requirements for the use of
grants received from the Account; authorizing the
installation of master key boxes at public and private
schools; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires: (1) the board of trustees of each school district and the
2 governing body of each charter school and private school to establish a
3 development committee to develop a plan to be used by the schools in the district or
4 the charter school or private school in responding to a crisis, emergency or suicide;
5 and (2) such a development committee to annually review and, as appropriate,
6 update the plan. (NRS 388.241, 388.245, 394.1685, 394.1688) Existing law creates
7 the Division of Emergency Management within the Office of the Military and
8 requires the Chief of the Division to carry out the program for emergency
9 management in this State. (NRS 414.040) Section 1 of this bill creates the Account
10 for the Nevada School Safety Data Grant Program within the Division to award
11 grants to law enforcement agencies in this State to procure school mapping data for
12 public schools located in the county in which the jurisdiction of the law
13 enforcement agency is located. Section 1: (1) authorizes a law enforcement agency
14 to apply for grants from the Program; (2) requires any grant money awarded from
15 the Program to be used for purposes of providing school mapping data by
16 contracting with a vendor to provide school mapping data; (3) requires an entity
