21 regulations to carry out the provisions of the Program. Sections 1 and 1.1 of this
22 bill prohibit the disclosure of school mapping data produced using a grant from the
23 Account except to employees of the school district, a public safety agency or the
24 Division.
25 Sections 1.3 and 1.7 of this bill authorize the board of trustees of a school
26 district or the governing body of a charter school or private school to provide for
27 the installation at the schools under the management of the board of trustees or the
28 governing body of a secure, exterior master key box meeting certain requirements.
29 Sections 1.3 and 1.7 require the board of trustees or the governing body to consult
30 with public safety agencies to determine the location to install the master key box.
31 Sections 1.5 and 1.9 of this bill make certain existing definitions relating to
32 emergency responses in schools applicable to sections 1.3 and 1.7.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 414 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Account for the Nevada School Safety Data Grant
4 Program is hereby created in the State General Fund. The Chief
5 or a designee of the Chief shall administer the Account. The
6 money in the Account must only be used for the purposes
7 described in subsection 5 and is hereby authorized for
8 expenditures as a continuing appropriation for those purposes.
9 2. The money in the Account that is provided from sources
10 other than the State General Fund must remain in the Account
11 and must not revert to the State General Fund at the end of any
12 fiscal year. Money in the Account that is appropriated or allocated
13 from the State General Fund must revert as provided in the
14 legislation that authorizes the appropriation or the allocation.
15 3. The Chief or designee may apply for and accept any gift,
16 donation, bequest, grant or other source of money for the use of
17 the Account. All money received for the use of the Account
18 pursuant to this subsection or from any other source must be
19 deposited with the State Treasurer for credit to the Account.
20 4. A political subdivision may make a grant of money for
21 credit to the Account. Such money must be used for the purposes
22 described in subsection 5, but solely with respect to public schools
23 located within the jurisdiction of the political subdivision.
24 5. A law enforcement agency, in consultation with the school
25 district in the county in which the law enforcement agency is
26 located, may apply to the Division for a grant of money from the
27 Account. A law enforcement agency receiving a grant of money
