1 from the Account shall use the money to provide school mapping
2 data for public schools in the jurisdiction of the law enforcement
3 agency for the purpose of facilitating an efficient and effective
4 response to emergencies in those public schools by public safety
5 agencies by contracting with a vendor to provide such school
6 mapping data.
7 6. The school mapping data provided pursuant to subsection
8 5 must:
9 (a) Be compatible with software platforms used by any
10 municipal, state or federal public safety agencies which are
11 responsible for providing emergency services to schools in the
12 school district without requiring a public safety agency to
13 purchase additional software or pay a fee to access the data;
14 (b) Be in a printable format in addition to an electronic or
15 digital format that can be integrated into an interactive mobile
16 platform in use by public safety agencies;
17 (c) Be verified for accuracy by the entity that produces the
18 school mapping data by a walk-through of the buildings and
19 grounds of the public school;
20 (d) Be oriented true north and overlaid with gridded x and y
21 coordinates for reference, and capture z-axis elevation data for
22 each floor of the public school;
23 (e) Contain site-specific labeling that matches the structure of
24 school buildings, including, without limitation, room labels,
25 hallway names, external doors or stairwell numbers, locations of
26 hazards, critical utility locations, key boxes, automated external
27 defibrillators and trauma kits;
28 (f) Contain site-specific labeling that matches the school
29 grounds, including, without limitation, parking areas, athletic
30 fields, surrounding roads and neighboring properties; and
31 (g) Be provided to the school district and public safety agencies
32 in the county in which the school district is located at no
33 additional cost beyond the initial cost of production of the school
34 mapping data.
35 7. A vendor that contracts with a law enforcement agency
36 pursuant to this section must:
37 (a) Comply with Special Publications 800-45, 800-53, 800-61
38 and 800-171 published by the National Institute of Standards and
39 Technology of the United States Department of Commerce.
40 (b) Ensure that all aspects of the process of creating school
41 mapping data are developed and maintained within the geographic
42 boundaries of the United States or any territory or possession
43 subject to the jurisdiction of the United States.
44 8. School mapping data produced pursuant to this section:
45 (a) Shall be deemed the property of the school district.
