14 (a) “Law enforcement agency” means an agency, office or
15 bureau of this State or a political subdivision of this State, the
16 primary duty of which is to enforce the law.
17 (b) “Public safety agency” has the meaning ascribed to it in
18 NRS 388.2345.
19 (c) “Public school” has the meaning ascribed to it in
20 NRS 385.007.
21 (d) “School mapping data” means structural data in a
22 printable format in addition to an electronic or digital format of
23 school buildings and grounds, including, without limitation, floor
24 plans, aerial imagery and site-specific labels identifying rooms,
25 hallways, stairwells and emergency resources to assist a public
26 safety agency in responding to emergencies at a public or private
27 school.
28 (e) “Software platforms” means the digital tools and systems
29 used by a public safety agency to access, share and use school
30 mapping data and related emergency information.
